o-retire-malaysia-cost-of-living-2025-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22He's%2070%20and%20thinks%20he%20would've%20had%20to%20continue%20working%20if%20he'd%20stayed%20in%20the%20US.%20Some%20older%20Americans%20are%20still%20punching%20the%20clock%20because%20they%20can't%20afford%20to%20retire.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22agoh%40businessinsider.com%20(Amanda%20Goh)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A192%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboomer-left-america-to-retire-malaysia-cost-of-living-2025-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20took%20a%207-month%20maternity%20leave%20from%20my%20Google%20engineering%20job.%20Coming%20back%20to%20work%20was%20the%20hardest%20thing%20I've%20ever%20done.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Photo%20collage%20of%20a%20woman%20surrounded%20by%20google%20and%20maternity%20leave%20imagery%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F678143a78951662c9f1f98b2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3Edecisiveimages%2FGetty%2C%20JARAMA%2FGetty%2C%20Chris%20Ryan%2FGetty%2C%20Yaroslav%20Kushta%2FGetty%2C%20Tyler%20Le%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EShruti%20Dhumak%20navigated%20maternity%20leave%20amid%20Google's%20AI%20industry%20shift%20and%20layoffs.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20split%20her%20leave%20to%20maintain%20visibility%20and%20manage%20family%20support%20from%20India.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDhumak%20focused%20on%20self-improvement%20and%20open%20communication%20to%20regain%20her%20work%20efficiency.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Shruti%20Dhumak%2C%20a%20cloud%20customer%20engineer%20in%20Google's%20Boston%20office%20who%20gave%20birth%20in%20February%202023.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%20Business%20Insider%20has%20verified%20her%20employment%20history.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20I%20had%20my%20son%2C%20I%20always%20doubted%20how%20I%20was%20going%20to%20manage%20being%20this%20overly%20ambitious%20person%20with%20motherhood.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20with%20Google%20for%20about%20four%20years.%20I%20had%20my%20first%20child%20in%20February%202022%20and%20split%20up%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmaternity-leave-misconceptions-holiday-working-mom-venture-capital-founder-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ematernity%20leave%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20three%20phases%20to%20make%20the%20most%20of%20temporary%20support%20I%20had%20when%20my%20family%20visited.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBetween%20Google's%20policy%20of%20six%20months%20of%20maternity%20leave%2C%20one%20month%20of%20prepartum%20leave%2C%20and%20one%20month%20of%20paid%20time%20off%2C%20I%20had%20a%20total%20of%20eight%20months%20of%20time%20away%20from%20work.%20I%20knew%20I%20was%20fortunate%20to%20have%20this%20time%20off%20because%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmaternity-leave-around-the-world-2018-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eis%20rare%20in%20the%20US%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20going%20on%20leave%20and%20the%20anxiety%20of%20being%20replaced%20while%20I%20was%20away%20was%20one%20of%20the%20hardest%20things%20I%20have%20dealt%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20a%20customer%20engineer%2C%20and%20a%20large%20part%20of%20my%20role%20revolves%20around%20managing%20relationships%20with%20our%20cloud%20clients.%20If%20someone%20takes%20over%20for%20me%2C%20the%20customers%20end%20up%20being%20closer%20to%20that%20representative%20and%20I%20risk%20losing%20my%20accounts%20to%20someone%20else.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20also%20paranoid%20that%20my%20absence%20or%20my%20performance%20below%20my%20peak%2C%20once%20I%20returned%2C%20would%20make%20me%20more%20susceptible%20to%20a%20layoff.%20Two%20weeks%20before%20my%20delivery%2C%20Google%20announced%20its%20biggest%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-layoffs-jobs-alphabet-work-employees-staff-sundar-pichai-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E12%2C000-people%20layoff%3C%2Fa%3E.%20As%20someone%20on%20an%20H1-B%20visa%2C%20a%20layoff%20would%20mean%20I%20would%20have%20to%20find%20another%20job%20in%20a%20matter%20of%20weeks%20or%20risk%20having%20to%20move%20back%20to%20India%20with%20a%20newborn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20came%20back%20to%20work%2C%20I%20was%20not%20a%20hundred%20percent%20myself%20%E2%80%94%20not%20as%20a%20person%20and%20not%20as%20an%20employee.%20I%20was%20not%20a%20hundred%20percent%20efficient.%20I've%20had%20my%20moments%20where%20I%20broke%20down%20and%20lost%20my%20train%20of%20thought%20during%20a%20call.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20my%20efforts%2C%20some%20other%20senior%20people%20were%20preferred%20by%20the%20business%20partners%20for%20some%20responsibilities.%20To%20add%20to%20it%2C%20Google%20was%20entering%20the%20artificial%20intelligence%20industry.%20Being%20away%20months%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3Efelt%20like%20I%20was%20behind%20by%20many%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20I%20was%20able%20to%20turn%20my%20performance%20around.%20In%202024%2C%20I%20got%20awards%20for%20my%20performance%2C%20and%20it's%20just%20the%20opposite%20of%20how%20last%20year%20went.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20four%20things%20I%20did%20to%20make%20the%20transition%20easier%20on%20myself%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221965c765-0d18-468d-848b-ba5321b7d469%5C%22%3E1.%20Split%20up%20my%20leave%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20offers%20employees%20the%20flexibility%20to%20take%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmom-denmark-one-year-paid-parental-leave-cut-short-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ematernity%20leave%20for%20up%20to%20a%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20the%20baby%20is%20born.%20I%20broke%20up%20my%20leave%20into%20three%20stages%2C%20which%20allowed%20me%20to